Amazing food and service! Cheers to this establishment and GM Jasmine Perales, And in particular Bryan who went above and beyond to give great service. Prior to coming, I spoke to GM Perales who generously offered to make the Birthday weekend special for my wife and group. We arrived on a really busy Valentines evening and was a bit concerned with the wait as my young adult kids had another venue to visit this All Star Weekend. Cue to Brian who basically took over from very pleasant Ethan and assured us we would enjoy great food, service and be on time. Sure enough as soon as we were seated, treats started coming over  with a round of Champaign and nice spring bruchetta appetizer on the house.  The meals were exquisite, the winner being the scallops in a cauliflower puré and zucchini. The gnocchi was a close second. Just as we thought  the meal couldn’t get better, we got the desserts that literally “takes the cake” here!! Amongst the chocolate cake, cheesecake and carrot cake (all given with homemade sorbet), the carrot cake really took the cake- carrot cake on top of whipped cream cheese icing with vanilla sorbet ice cream. BTW Bryan very generously paid for one of our desserts which is really rare and is a sign of an exceptional restaurant and staff when this is done (we tipped as if everything was included). So delicious were the desserts , they should win an award!! Would highly recommend coming here for the food, service, and especially the deserts!!!  My complements to GM Perales and her staff. She came around frequently to check on us. GM Jasmine and Bryan YOU ROCK!!!

This place is fantastic! We came from Minneapolos on a long weekend to Chicago. My boyfriend and I planned to visit specifically this restaurant for the oysters after reading about other seafood restaurants in the city. The restaurant is nicely decorated and the small space is used well. Not overly crowded but still ample seating for many guests. Our server was very knowledgeable about the menu offerings and had suggestions when we asked questions. My boyfriend really only likes cooked oysters, while I don't discriminate. She advised of some cooked options for him that weren't actually on the menu for the evening. The oysters were all delicious of course. I also had the scallops for a main course. The plate was a bit small for my liking but the flavors were incredible. The scallops were cooked just so, they seemed to melt in my mouth. I also had sherberts for dessert, blood orange which was quite tart but delicious, mango which was sweet and delicious, and coconut which had texture almost like ice cream and it was incredible. Well worth the drive from Minneapolis!

What an amazing start to our vacation in Chicago!  The service was impeccable from start to finish. Our server, Joseph, was attentive, friendly, and made great suggestions. We appreciated the attention to detail by all the staff.  They surprised us with a complimentary fish of the day. The fish was moist.  We had the mussels which were plump and juicy, the smoked fish platter that had a nice selection of fish and garnishes, the broccoli (recommended by Joseph) which was light and refreshing, and the soba had a good contrast in textures and flavors. For dessert, we had the brownie that was evenly balanced between the marshmallows, raspberry sorbet, and honeycomb.

My husband and I had this restaurant on our list of places to dine in Chicago. We heard good reviews about this place and chose this eatery to celebrate our 9yr wedding anniversary.  This was the best decision we made!!! For starters we shared the bruschetta shrimp/avocado, clam chowder soup and a garden of fresh/charred broccoli. For dinner we had crabcake, fish tacos and the lobster roll. For dessert we shared the pb & jelly panna cotta and the carrot cake.  The fish tacos were ok but everything else was divine, delicious, scrumptious...i never had a meal where every dish raise the bar!!!  You've to eat here..even if you live out of state, buy a ticket and just fly into Chicago to only eat @ this restaurant.  As for the service, our waiter was warm, friendly and he made our dining experience even more special..  I will be back..
